\par }{\b\fs22\cf2 Moon}{\fs24 
\par \tab  
\par \tab This deity is a god of inspiration, magic, and mystery, and is closely related to the god of Darkness (see above). 
\par \tab His priests celebrate the magics and light granted by the moon.
\par \tab In a fantasy setting, there could be numerous gods of the moon... one for each of several moons the planet possesses.
\par \tab Most moon-gods are female.
\par \tab The priests of this god are on good terms with the priests of Darkness/Night, Dawn, Hunting, Light, Magic, Oracles/Prophecy, and Sun.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Alignment:}{\fs24  The deity is true neutral. The priests may be neutral evil, true neutral, or neutral good; evil priests have their own sect and the other priests don't have to tolerate them. The flock may be of any alignment.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Minimum Ability Scores:}{\fs24  Wisdom 10. Wisdom 16 means +10% experience.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Races Allowed:}{\fs24  Elves, gnomes, half-elves, halflings, humans.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Nonweapon and Weapon Proficiencies:}{\fs24 
 Nonweapon Proficiencies Required: Navigation. Nonweapon Proficiencies Recommended: Astrology, Reading/Writing, Religion, Spellcraft. Weapon Proficiencies Required: Nonweapon Proficiency Group Crossovers: Priest, General.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Duties of the Priest:}{\fs24 
 Guidance, Marriage. Education: These priests help in the promotion and teaching of magic. These priests must participate in celebrations of the god, which take place once each moon (different temples may celebrate on the full moon or the n
ew moon, at the DM's option).
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Weapon and Armor Restrictions:}{\fs24  Weapons Permitted: Bows (all), dagger/dirk, dart, javelin, knife, sling, spear. Armor Permitted: All non-metal armor; any shield that is circular or crescent-shaped. Oriental Campaigns: Also dai
