 Weapons Permitted: Dagger/dirk, javelin, knife, lasso, quarterstaff, spear, stiletto, sword/long, sword/rapier, sword/sabre. Armor Permitted: None; no shields. Oriental Campaigns: Also bo stick, chain, katana. All together, these constitute Medium combat
 abilities.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Other Limitations:}{\fs24  Priests of this sect receive six-sided dice for hit points, not eight-sided.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Spheres of Influence:}{\fs24  Major Access to All, Animal, Charm, Summoning, Sun. Minor Access to Divination, Elemental, Healing, Plant.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Powers:}{\fs24   }{\i\fs24 Charm/Fascination}{\fs24  (as per the Designing Faiths chapter). }{\i\fs24 Soothing Word}{\fs24  (as per the Designing Faiths chapter, but at 5th level can use the power six times per day instead of three). }{
\i\fs24 Turn Undead}{\fs24  (same as the Cleric ability).
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Followers and Strongholds:}{\fs24  The follower
s are received at 7th level, and consist of three third-level priests and six first-level priests of the same order, plus five first-level fighters to act as temple guards and twenty Normal Men and Women, each of whom has a Nonweapon Proficiency appropria
