\par }{\b\fs22\cf2 Thunder
\par }{\fs24 \tab  
\par \tab 
The thunder-god is very similar to the lightning-god; in campaigns where they both exist, they will probably be related, even brothers. He represents the fearsomeness of nature, natural forces at their most frightening, and so is a god of terror and f
ear as well. Like the lightning-god, he is also a god of storms.
\par \tab Also as with the lightning-god, the thunder-god is not very concerned with the affairs of mortals; he lets them worship him and grants power to his priests, but otherwise doesn't interfere m
uch in mortal affairs. His priests promote worship of his power and fearsomeness, especially as traits which the followers wish to use against their enemies. 
\par \tab The thunder-god is male.
\par \tab The priests of this god are on good terms with the priests of Elemental Forces, Lightning (especially), Nature, Race (Dwarven), Sky/Weather, and Strength.
\par \tab }{\b\fs24 Alignment:}{\fs24  The deity is true neutral. The priests may be neutral evil, true neutral, or neutral good; evil priests have their own sect and the other priests don't have to tolerate them. The flock may be of any alignment.
